# =============================================================================
# Database Table Structure (For Reference)
# =============================================================================
# Make sure your Supabase database has these tables:

# Table: pool_candles
# - timestamp (bigint) - Unix timestamp
# - price (decimal) - Pool price
# - volume (decimal) - Trading volume
# - address (text) - Pool contract address
# - interval (text) - Time interval (e.g., '3600000' for 1 hour)

# Table: pools (optional for pools.info operation)
# - address (text) - Pool contract address
# - name (text) - Pool name
# - token0 (text) - First token symbol
# - token1 (text) - Second token symbol
# - fee (decimal) - Pool fee
# - created_at (timestamp) - Creation date

# =============================================================================
# Quick Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp env.example .env

# 2. Get your Supabase credentials:
#    - Go to https://app.supabase.com
#    - Create/select your project
#    - Go to Settings > API
#    - Copy the Project URL and anon public key

# 3. Update .env with your actual values

# 4. Test the setup:
#    npm test

# 5. Test with mock data (no Supabase needed):
#    npm run getCandlesFromPool -- --pool 0x123... --mock

# 6. Test with real Supabase data:
#    npm run getCandlesFromPool -- --pool 0xF336F812Db1ad142F22A9A4dd43D40e64B478361 